# Root environment example for `docker compose`.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. Variables left blank will have NO default for
# secrets — run `make setup` to auto-generate a secure .env on first install.
# This file is committed; `.env` is gitignored and must NOT be committed.

# --- MinIO (object storage) ---
# SECURITY: never use the old default minioadmin / minioadmin in any real
# deployment. `make setup` generates a unique MINIO_ROOT_USER and
# MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD and writes them to .env. ROTATE these credentials on
# first deploy. If the default pair (minioadmin/minioadmin) is detected,
# the backend refuses to use MinIO and stores files on local disk instead.
# Left blank here so `make setup` / docker compose require real values.
MINIO_ROOT_USER=
MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=
